First_Text: 39 key drugs in the market approved before 2010,3 key drugs with new mechanisms approved in the last 5 years
Second_Text: This table provides a view of drugs available for theraoy (based on approval by FDA) over the years as well as the companies sponsoring these drugs
Third_Text: The number of new drugs approved in the recent past helps assess the viability of new development of science of therapy in this area
Forth_Text: It is also instructive to look for periods of time with little or no approval activity. A further deep dive into what trials were preceding this time frame and what companies were involved may be insightful from a competitive analysis perspective

First_Text: The plot on the right shares the number of drugs approved by various companies. (In some cases, the companies may be listed in different versions of their names or their subsidiaries - the number of approvals in this case is additive)
Second_Text: The plot is an easy way to assess the level of engagement that companies have with this disease area and which companies have been leaders in development of approved therapies

Left.Header: Drugs Approved by Mechanisms of Action
First_Text: The plot on the right shares the number of drugs approved using different Mechanisms of Action.
Second_Text: The plot is an easy way to assess the mechanisms of action and targets that have been successful in treating this disease area.
Third_Text: Further analysis of the evolution of the success of these Mechanisms of Action and which companies have driven them are also possible using KnolChat.

First_Text: The table on the right shares the approved drugs and their co-indications for which they are approved by the FDA
Second_Text: Additional assessment of the stages for which they are approved are accessible in the Module titled Landscape: Indication

First_Text: These set of plots show the breakdown of Clinical trials sponsored by the industry for this indication. Compare completed studies (showing the history of trials and engagement) as well as active studies. The break-up by phase also points to the strength of the current development pipeline.
Second_Text: One can monitor new studies being initiated or completion of studies through the eponymous module.

Left.Header: Approval and Termination Statistics for Clinical Studies in Acne
First_Text: This plot shows the phase-wise breakup of clinical trials for the indication. For each phase it shows the break-up of trials by their status. The active or ongoing trials point to the strength of the current pipeline. The size of the terminated and withdrawn trials point to current or historic difficulty in running trials for this indication.
Second_Text: Additional analysis of ongoing trials is accessible via KnolChat

First_Text: This plot shows the phase-wise breakup of interventional clinical trials for the indication over time. It reflects the focus and the market interest in this indication by companies. Additionally, the comparative evolution by phase is interesting in assessing progress of drug development.
Second_Text: Additional analysis of ongoing trials include assessment of evolving engagement by companies, and by Mechanism of Action. These can be further explored using KnolChat

Left.Header: Drug Development by Mechanism of Action
First_Text: This plot shows the number of clinical trials for the indication by Mechanism of Action (MoA). The user can zoom in / out to focus on which MoA have been used and how often in development therapies for this indication.
Second_Text: Additional analysis of phase wise breakup of these studies by Mechanism of Action, companies which favored certain MoA or the use of MoA for this indication over time can be undertaken. These can be further explored using KnolChat

First_Text: A further breakup of the nature of involvement of these companies - number of companies in various phase of drug development, and the type of companies - helps get better sense of the business backing to new drug development in this therapeutic area.
Second_Text: Additional analysis of the success of these companies, their strategies and the strength of their pipelines are available in the Landscape Modules

First_Text: This plot shows the number of clinical trials for the indication by Companies. The user can zoom in / out to focus on which companies are involved and how many trials they have sponsored.
Second_Text: Additional analysis of phase wise breakup of these studies by companies, which MoA they favored, how successful they were or their interest in this indication over time can be undertaken. These can be further explored using KnolChat
